22/05/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Belgrade is hosting the annual EBRD summit that began Friday (20 May) and will run through Sunday. EBRD President Jean Lemierre said the bank chose Belgrade for the two-day meeting in order to encourage continued economic reforms and positive changes in the region. On Friday, the EBRD agreed to provide two loans, totaling 88m euros, to Serbia-Montenegro. Meanwhile, the European Investment Bank said it would provide Serbia with a 251m-euro loan, to be used for building new schools and improving transportation systems. (Politika - 22/05/05; Danas, AP - 21/05/05; B92, AP - 20/05/05)
